# 📸 Visual Gallery — AI Drift Detection Capstone

This folder contains static, high-resolution visuals featured in the main project README.  
Each figure highlights a different dimension of the drift-detection framework, from detection to interpretation and strategic context.

| File | Description | Data Source | Generated By |
|------|--------------|--------------|---------------|
| **capstone_banner.png** | Project banner displayed at the top of the repo | N/A | Canva / PowerPoint |
| **drift_heatmap.png** | Monthly feature drift intensity (KS-statistic) | Synthetic / anonymized LendingClub data | visuals_code/drift_heatmap.py |
| **reconstruction_error.png** | Autoencoder reconstruction error trend (drift spikes) | Synthetic / anonymized LendingClub data | visuals_code/reconstruction_error.py |
| **feature_drift.png** | Top features influencing drift (SHAP summary) | Synthetic / anonymized LendingClub data | visuals_code/feature_drift.py |
| **drift_timeseries.png** | Aggregate drift magnitude over time | Synthetic / anonymized LendingClub data | visuals_code/drift_timeseries.py |
| **macro_overlay.png** | Overlay of macro indicators vs drift magnitude | Synthetic macro + anonymized LendingClub data | visuals_code/macro_overlay.py |

> **Note:** All data visualized here is either synthetic or anonymized for educational and demonstration purposes.  
> To reproduce the charts, run the corresponding script inside `/visuals_code/`.

---

## 💡 Design Standards
- Resolution: **180 dpi**, width ≈ 1200 px  
- Font: **DejaVu Sans** (consistent across all visuals)  
- Color themes: *coolwarm*, *steelblue*, *lightcoral*, *gray*  
- Export format: `.png` only (for GitHub readability)

---

### 🏁 Quick Reference
- Primary visuals displayed in main `README.md` under **📊 Visualizations**  
- Secondary or alternative visuals (experimental versions) may be added here later with `_v2` suffixes  
  e.g. `drift_heatmap_v2.png`, `feature_drift_detail.png`
